name: r-plumber
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.2.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-plumber
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/plumber_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/plumber/plumber_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: eca9464622666033270ec0d9c86a7101360f041432db2932433bcc9c5ddfc0d1

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-r6 >=2.0.0
    - r-crayon
    - r-ellipsis >=0.3.0
    - r-httpuv >=1.5.0
    - r-jsonlite >=0.9.16
    - r-lifecycle >=0.2.0
    - r-magrittr
    - r-mime
    - r-promises >=1.1.0
    - r-rlang
    - r-sodium
    - r-stringi >=0.3.0
    - r-swagger >=3.33.0
    - r-webutils >=1.1
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-r6 >=2.0.0
    - r-crayon
    - r-ellipsis >=0.3.0
    - r-httpuv >=1.5.0
    - r-jsonlite >=0.9.16
    - r-lifecycle >=0.2.0
    - r-magrittr
    - r-mime
    - r-promises >=1.1.0
    - r-rlang
    - r-sodium
    - r-stringi >=0.3.0
    - r-swagger >=3.33.0
    - r-webutils >=1.1

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('plumber')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('plumber')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://www.rplumber.io (site) https://github.com/trestletech/plumber (dev)
  license: MIT
  summary: Gives the ability to automatically generate and serve an HTTP API from R functions using the annotations in the R documentation around your functions.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - koverholt
